Wing expanse: 
<quantity box="[554,633,1931,1959]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="1" pageNumber="388" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[648,716,1931,1958]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,176,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1427,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1, Botyodes asialis, ♂, NE India, Mizoram, 2, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram; 3, Botyodes principalis, ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 4, ditto, ♀, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh; 5, Neobotyodes crocopteralis, gen. &amp; comb. nov., ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 6, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255391/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1436,1931,2030]" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">
<emphasis box="[199,260,1968,1994]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="388">Head</emphasis>
. Vertex fuscous brown, under side white, distinct scales at proboscis. Antennae of males simple, slightly shorter than costal length of forewings.
</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255391/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" startId="2.[151,264,1924,1949]" targetBox="[166,1413,176,1895]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1924,2021]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,314,1924,1949]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">FIGURES 1–6.</emphasis>
Adults. 1, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Guenee" authorityYear="1854" box="[424,589,1925,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="asialis">
<emphasis box="[424,589,1925,1949]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Botyodes asialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, NE India, Mizoram, 2, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram; 3, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Leech" authorityYear="1889" box="[1190,1399,1925,1949]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Botyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="principalis">
<emphasis box="[1190,1399,1925,1949]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Botyodes principalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 4, ditto, ♀, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh; 5, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Singh &amp; Kirti &amp; Singh &amp; Ranjan" authorityYear="2019" baseAuthorityName="Hampson" baseAuthorityYear="1898" box="[917,1188,1961,1985]" class="Insecta" family="Crambidae" genus="Neobotyodes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="389" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crocopteralis">
<emphasis box="[917,1188,1961,1985]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">Neobotyodes crocopteralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1202,1397,1960,1985]" pageId="2" pageNumber="389">gen. &amp; comb. nov.</emphasis>
, ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 6, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis box="[199,280,153,179]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Thorax</emphasis>
. Forewings fuscous brown with an oblique, orange-yellow broad band from middle of costa to anal angle; slightly constricted at middle. Hindwings uniformly fuscous brown. 
<emphasis box="[993,1099,189,215]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Black.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis box="[199,367,225,251]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Male genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[386,527,225,251]" captionStart="FIGURES 19–23" captionStartId="5.[151,264,1739,1764]" captionTargetBox="[157,1436,187,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,181,1719]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURES 19–23. Male genitalia. 19, 20, Neobotyodes crocopteralis, gen. &amp; comb. nov. 21–23, Caldubotys caldusalis gen. &amp; comb. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255397/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Figs. 19–20</figureCitation>
). Uncus short, almost rectangular with a minute notch at apex, edges setosed; tegumen short; valvae narrow, elongated, tongue shaped, a strong thumb like process from basal half of inner wall; juxta with two broad apical arms; vesica with a curved cornutus having two spines at apex and another long ray of compactly placed small spines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" box="[199,657,369,396]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,369,395]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Female.</emphasis>
Wing expanse: 
<quantity box="[473,555,369,395]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="390" unit="mm" value="37.0">37 mm</quantity>
. (
<figureCitation box="[574,643,369,396]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–6" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1924,1949]" captionTargetBox="[166,1413,176,1895]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1427,166,1905]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–6. Adults. 1, Botyodes asialis, ♂, NE India, Mizoram, 2, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram; 3, Botyodes principalis, ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 4, ditto, ♀, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh; 5, Neobotyodes crocopteralis, gen. &amp; comb. nov., ♂, NE India, Arunachal Pradesh, 6, ditto, ♀, NE India, Mizoram." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255391/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" box="[199,885,405,431]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis box="[199,267,405,431]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Head.</emphasis>
Vertex bright golden-yellow; palpi black, white below.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis box="[199,280,441,467]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Thorax</emphasis>
. Forewings orange with fuscous brown ante-medial spot on median nervure, a reniform at disco-cellular, a post-medial spot below vein Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[599,607,494,508]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">2</subScript>
, whole apical area fuscous brown with rounded inner edge, underside of forewing having basal part of costal area suffused with black. Hindwings with post-medial black spot above vein M 
<subScript attach="left" box="[176,184,566,580]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">2</subScript>
, having specks above and below it; a spot below vein Cu 
<subScript attach="left" box="[827,835,566,580]" fontSize="6" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">2</subScript>
, having speck below it.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" box="[199,659,585,611]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis box="[199,305,585,611]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Yellow, with black irrorations.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,153,792]" box="[199,1280,621,647]" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">
<emphasis box="[199,390,621,647]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Female genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[405,488,621,647]" captionStart="FIGURES 29–32" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1968,1993]" captionTargetBox="[168,1420,857,1937]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[151,1436,844,1949]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 29–32. Female genitalia, 29, Botyodes asialis; 30, Botyodes principalis; 31, Neobotyodes crocopteralis, gen. &amp; comb. nov.; 32, Caldubotys caldusalis, gen. &amp; comb. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3255401/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="390">Fig. 31</figureCitation>
). Ductus bursae wrinkly sclerotised; corpus bursae membranous, oval.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
